# Arkn Framework Rules

## Result<T> — never throw

All domain/service/application methods **must** return `Result` or `Result<T>`.

```csharp
// ✅
public Result<User> GetUser(Guid id)
{
    var user = _repo.Find(id);
    return user is null
        ? Error.NotFound("User.NotFound", $"User {id} not found.")
        : Result.Success(user);
}

// ❌ never do this
public User GetUser(Guid id) => _repo.Find(id) ?? throw new Exception("not found");
```

## Error codes — Namespace.Reason

```csharp
Error.NotFound("User.NotFound", "...")       // ✅
Error.Validation("Order.QuantityInvalid", "...") // ✅
Error.NotFound("user_not_found", "...")      // ❌
```

## Consuming Result

```csharp
// ✅ in endpoints
return result.Match(
    onSuccess: dto  => Ok(dto),
    onFailure: err  => err.Type switch
    {
        ErrorType.NotFound   => NotFound(),
        ErrorType.Validation => BadRequest(err.Message),
        _                    => Problem(err.Message)
    });

// ✅ chaining
var result = GetOrder(id).Map(o => o.ToDto());

// ❌ never access .Value without checking .IsSuccess
```

## Jobs

```csharp
// ✅
public class MyJob : IArknJob
{
    public async Task<Result> ExecuteAsync(CancellationToken ct) { ... }
}
// ❌ Task without Result is invalid
```

## Analyzers (compile-time enforcement)

ARK001 — methods must return Result | ARK002 — error code format | ARK003 — no silent discard | ARK004 — job return type
